    "Its behavioral repertoire is now smaller, and certain opportunities for interactions are just no longer possible.",
    "13 What grounds these differences?",
    "The answer this paper suggests points to the double nature of affective artificial agents.",
    "Since affective artificial agents are agents, they not only have to relate with the world surrounding them (human users included), but they have to do so in a way that is relevant to the emotivity of their users.",
